On February 25, a chartered plane landed in Beijing Capital International Airport, Beijing, as the extended Chinese New Year holiday affected by the outbreak ended.

The plane departed from France, where it shipped parts for CT machines to China from suppliers and factories in Europe for GE healthcare, a multinational medical device maker.

Normally, the plane has a capacity of 100 tons, but it is only carrying more than 30 tons, which means it will lose more than 60% of its capacity on this flight. From a business point of view, this is not a good choice, after all, it will directly drive up costs.

But for now, cost is not the issue. The CT components from the global supply chain arrived in Beijing Capital International Airport and quickly started a relay race.

Beijing Capital International Airport Customs officers who have been on duty during the Spring Festival ensure that imported goods are inspected at any time. Enterprises complete customs clearance applications online 2-3 days in advance. After the arrival of goods, the customs clearance time is from the previous 2-3 days, to "zero latency. ". Then, the Customs Department of Yizhuang Economic Development Zone, where GE medical's Beijing imaging equipment manufacturing base is located, took over the baton, simplifying the approval process and compressing the half-day approval process to an hour.

Customs clearance complete. Some of the parts were immediately sent to GE medical Beijing imaging equipment manufacturing base, rapid assembly. As soon as three days later, these parts and components of the CT equipment will be shipped, 1,100 km away to Wuhan.

Clinically, doctors need to combine CT findings to determine whether a patient has NCP.

In order to meet the needs of the construction of the emergency isolation area and treatment facilities in the Shelter Hospital, GE medical has designed an integrated CT examination room for the shelter, ge Medical Offers Deep Sky CT scans that avoid patient contact and use AI to improve efficiency.

"In the next two weeks, GE medical will successively deliver 20 sets of one-piece CT examination rooms in 19 Wuhan square-cabin hospitals, including the Wuhan Sports Center Stadium and Huangpi Yizhong Gymnasium, to help Wuhan cope with the rapid and accurate diagnosis of new coronary pneumonia, " Chen Heqiang, general manager of GE medical's Beijing imaging equipment manufacturing base, told interface news.

Among CT equipment manufacturers, GE healthcare leads China with a market share of 33.15 percent, according to medcnet.

Ge Medical Beijing imaging equipment manufacturing base is one of the most important manufacturing bases for GE medical imaging equipment in the world. The equipment it produces covers various kinds of equipment, including CT, x-ray machines, breast machines and interventional surgical machines, to the global market. Among them especially with CT equipment, about 70% of the global CT equipment are from GE medical Beijing factory.

But CT production is also the product of the typical global manufacturing division of Labor. A CT device requires 6,000 components and involves more than 150 suppliers worldwide, compared with more than 80 in China.

Ge Healthcare's charter flight is the first time the medical-device giant has used a charter flight to connect the global supply chain.

The outbreak of the new crown disease has boosted demand for CT SCANS, and for a month, GE medical's Beijing Plant has received 200 emergency orders in addition to its regular orders. Half of them are from Hubei, the other half from Guangdong, Zhejiang and other places in the Shelter Hospital, General Hospital, and the number is still growing.

After the outbreak in China, many airlines stopped flying to China and there was a serious shortage of international air capacity. With the recent resumption of domestic enterprises, import and export demand recovery, the problem of insufficient capacity will be further highlighted.

Ge Medical Beijing imaging equipment manufacturing base for parts and components required by domestic and foreign upstream manufacturers of parts and components import and export will face great uncertainty.

"We started thinking about charter flights around February 10, " Jeff Miao, senior China Logistics Manager at Ge Healthcare, told interface news.

But GE medical has no experience in how charter flights work.

Charter connecting the supply chain, in addition to the global production team, order management team, but also to external coordination of the supply chain, logistics and freight customs, freight forwarders alone to communicate with Europe, China, the United States freight forwarders.

"A while ago, I had meetings with colleagues all over the world, basically working until 1 a.m. to sort out all the processes, " Miao said. Chartered aircraft in the solution of capacity and timeliness, but also greatly increased transport costs. The quick response in short time will lead to the increase of logistics operation risk. Nonetheless, the plan quickly gained the support of GE healthcare's top global leaders.

Seven days after the discussion, on February 17, GE medical decided to charter a flight.

For the four weeks after February 25, GE medical's charter flights will fly "france-beijing-chicago-beijing-france" four times a week, two in and two out of Beijing.

The screening of suspected cases and follow-up of patients are urgent. Under the Emergency Situation, GE medical has greatly adjusted the production process. Beijing's economic and Trade Commission gave the factory a "Road Map, " a sign that GE medical and upstream suppliers were communicating back to work, helping them tap into domestic supply.

"At present, the upstream supply chain suppliers have resumed work, but the problem is that the demand of the epidemic is not normal demand, it is double demand, so it is also more than the original capacity demand for the suppliers, " Chen said.

On a typical day, it takes two to three weeks for a CT to ship from a tissue fitting to a factory. But that rhythm is no longer allowed under the new crown. On the third day of the first lunar month (January 27) , GE medical received a CT order from Raytheon Hospital for the deep eye, requiring equipment to enter within a week.

Since then, the base has been on a 24 hour, 24 hour, three day, two night production of a deep eye CT, which was installed at the time of delivery at Mount Thor Hospital.

Conventional Orders, the production line first to ensure the highest efficiency, the best labor, but emergency orders no longer take these needs into account, a part out of stock, we have to "party" . "workers have to wait. It's a relatively high cost of production, and you lose some of your productivity, but that's not up for discussion. The situation is that we are concentrating resources around the world to help China meet the very urgent needs of the epidemic, so the cost is no longer the primary factor for us to consider,"Chen said.

In fact, the cost of overloading the factory to ensure that production of not only Beijing imaging equipment manufacturing base, GE healthcare global factories are tilted to China's resources, "If Chinese demand is still relatively high, we ask them [ global factories ] to place additional orders to help with production, " Miao said.

European suppliers are also in the Minute to Win It. Europe's blood-vessel-like road logistics will integrate GE healthcare's scattered plants and suppliers in Norway, Austria and Finland into France ahead of schedule, with shipments to China on standby charter flights. Once unloaded in Beijing Capital International Airport, the plane will once again set off to take Chinese parts to Chicago, Florida, where they will once again be dispersed to the multinational's factories around the world.

The production of CT equipment is finished, and the difficulties of ground traffic control need to be solved.

In early February, there was a heavy snowfall in Beijing, the same day GE medical had several CT equipment to be shipped from the Beijing Factory. The Beijing Economic and Technological Development Area arranged for a snowplow to arrive at the plant, and after a quick snow removal, the truck was able to make a smooth start. In addition to the weather, which has made transportation difficult, the cost of ground logistics has also risen sharply as a result of the outbreak.

And installation is a difficult problem, Raytheon Mountain Hospital requires 7 days to complete the order delivery and installation. In this process, the health and safety of the local service team must be ensured, but also fast enough. Since the Spring Festival, GE medical field engineers in the anti-epidemic front to complete a variety of emergency installation and commissioning tasks.

On February 28, Liang Wannian, head of the National Health Commission's Expert Group on Epidemic Response and disposal, said that the epidemic had been effectively contained in Hubei, with the exception of Wuhan. Chen also hopes that this unusual pace of work can be concluded as soon as possible.

"I hope that after the Qingming Festival, we will have a better momentum in April according to the information released by the National Health Commission, " Chen said.
